==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pend
<hw>Pend</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Pended</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pending</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>pendere</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To hang; to depend.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Pending</qex> upon certain powerful motions.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be undecided, or in process of
adjustment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pend</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Pend
<hw>Pend</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <ets>pen</ets> to shut in, or
AS. <ets>pyndan</ets>, E. <ets>pound</ets> an inclosure.]</ety> <def>To
pen; to confine.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
